CODA-19 Data Model



Table culture_data
IdxField NameData TypeDescription
* patient_site_uid char(128) Identifier referencing a specific individual in the patient_data table.
* culture_data_id integer Primary key of this table; implemented as an auto-incrementing integer.
  culture_type text Type of culture obtained. Possible values: "bacterial_aerobic", "bacterial_anaerobic", "mycobacterial", "fungal", "viral".
  culture_result_status text Current status of the culture. Possible values: "resulted", "pending", "cancelled".
  culture_loinc_code text LOINC code of the culture being performed.
  culture_sample_type text Site from which the culture sample was collected. Possible values: "blood", "urine", "expectorated_sputum", "bronchial_aspirate", "pleural_fluid", "ascites_fluid", "cerebrospinal_fluid", etc.
  culture_sample_time timestamp Timestamp indicating the time at which the culture was sampled.
  culture_result_time timestamp Timestamp indicating the time at which the culture was resulted.
  culture_gram_positive text Whether or not Gram stain was positive. Possible values: "positive", "negative".
  culture_growth_result text Whether or not culture yielded growth of a pathogen in significant quantities (e.g. any quantity for blood, > 10^3 CFUs for LBA sputum). Possible values: "positive", "negative".
  culture_result_organisms boolean Comma-separated list of organisms that have grown on the culture medium. Organisms should be stated with their full name (e.g. Staphylococcus aureus).


Table diagnosis_data
IdxField NameData TypeDescription
* patient_site_uid char(128) Identifier referencing a specific individual in the patient_data table.
episode_data_id integer Identifier referencing episode during which a diagnosis was made.
* diagnosis_data_id integer Primary key of this table; implemented as an auto-incrementing integer.
  diagnosis_type text Type of diagnosis recorded. Possible values:
"previous_comorbidity" (BDCP type 1)
"new_comorbidity" (BDCP type 2)
"principal_diagnosis" (BDCP type M)
"secondary_diagnosis" (BDCP type 3)
"death" (not a BDCP type)

Reference: Canadian Norms for Codification of Medical Diagnoses, https://bit.ly/346yCHg
  diagnosis_name text Name of diagnosis that was recorded, as derived from ICD code.
  diagnosis_icd_code text ICD-10 code referencing the diagnosis.
  diagnosis_source text Data source system from which the diagnosis was recorded. For local institutional usage.
  diagnosis_time timestamp Timestamp indicating when the diagnosis was made.


Table drug_data
IdxField NameData TypeDescription
* patient_site_uid char(128) Identifier referencing a specific individual in the patient_data table.
* drug_data_id integer
  drug_name text Generic name of drug that was administered. Name should be in lowercase letters, in English format, with no accents.
  drug_din_code text Standard Drug Identification Number (DIN).

Reference: https://bit.ly/2R8jPGC
  drug_class text Standard drug class.
  drug_infusion boolean True if the drug is administered via a continuous infusion.
  drug_dose text Dose of the drug administered at a time.
  drug_rate text Drug infusion rate, for continuous infusions.
  drug_roa text Drug route of administration short name, as defined by FDA standards (e.g. IV, SC, PO). N.B. IV DRIP is not used; information on whether the drug is administered as an continuous infusion is found in the drug_infusion column.

Reference: https://bit.ly/3dRlo5z
  drug_frequency text Frequency of drug administration, in text format.
  drug_start_time timestamp Timezone, with timestamp, indicating the time at which the drug was started.
  drug_end_time timestamp Timezone, with timestamp, indicating the time at which the drug was stopped.


Table episode_data

Start and end type of patient presence on unit, with accompanying metadata.

IdxField NameData TypeDescription
* patient_site_uid char(128) Identifier referencing a specific individual in the patient_data table.
* episode_data_id integer Primary key of this table; implemented as an auto-incrementing integer.
  episode_unit_type text Type of unit where the patient was present during this episode. Possible values: "intensive_care_unit", "high_dependency_unit", "coronary_care_unit", "inpatient_ward", "emergency_room", "day_surgery_unit", "other".
  episode_ctas smallint CTAS (Canadian Triage and Acuity Scale) level for initial presentation in ER.
Level 1 = Resuscitation
Level 2 = Emergent
Level 3 = Urgent
Level 4 = Less urgent
Level 5 = Non urgent

Should be blank unless episode_unit_type is "emergency_room"
  episode_start_time timestamp Timestamp indicating when the episode started (e.g. triaged in the emergency room).
  episode_end_time timestamp Timestamp of when the episode ended (e.g. discharged from the emergency room).
  episode_description text Free text description of the reason for the episode.
  episode_duration_hours integer Total duration of the episode, in hours. Rounded down to the nearest integer.


Table exposure_data

Exposure dates and types.

IdxField NameData TypeDescription
* patient_site_uid char(128) Identifier referencing a specific individual in the patient_data table.
* exposure_data_id integer Primary key of this table; implemented as an auto-incrementing integer.
exposure_type_id integer Identifier representing the type of exposure.
  exposure_cumulative float Cumulative exposure, if quantifiable. E.g. number of pack years smoked.
  exposure_details text Free text with additional details on exposure.
  exposure_start_time timestamp Timestamp, with time zone, indicating when the exposure occurred (for a one-time exposure), or started (for an prolonged exposure).
  exposure_end_time timestamp Timestamp, with time zone, indicating when the exposure ended.


Table exposure_type
IdxField NameData TypeDescription
* exposure_type_id integer Primary key of this table; implemented as an auto-incrementing integer.
  exposure_type_name text Name of exposure type.
  exposure_type_description text Description of exposure.
  exposure_type_cumulative_units text Units determining how the exposure is cumulated (e.g. pack-years for smoking).


Table imaging_data
IdxField NameData TypeDescription
* patient_site_uid char(128) Identifier referencing a specific individual in the patient_data table.
* imaging_data_id integer Primary key of this table; implemented as an auto-incrementing integer.
  imaging_accession_uid char(128) Hashed accession number of the imaging on the site's local PACS database.
  imaging_status text Status of the imaging. Can be "read", "pending", "destroyed"
  imaging_modality text Modality of the imaging that was performed, as defined by the DICOM "Modality" header (DICOM standard section C.7.3.1). Lowercase letters.

Examples: "ct", "xr", "us".

Reference: https://bit.ly/2X8Yv7Q
  imaging_body_site text Body site that was imaged. E.g. "chest".
  imaging_iv_contrast boolean True if intravenous contrast was given during the imaging study.
  imaging_manufacturer text Manufacturer of the equipment that was used to acquire imaging, as defined by the DICOM "Manufacturer header."
  imaging_acquisition_time timestamp Timestamp representing the time at which the study was performed.
  imaging_report_time timestamp Timestamp indicating the time at which the imaging was reported.
  imaging_report_text text De-identified textual report of the imaging.


Table intervention_data
IdxField NameData TypeDescription
* patient_site_uid char(128) Identifier referencing a specific individual in the patient_data table.
drug_data_id integer
* intervention_data_id integer Primary key of this table; implemented as an auto-incrementing integer.
intervention_type_id integer Identifier referencing the type of intervention.
  intervention_details text Free text, detailing additional details about the intervention that was performed.
  intervention_start_time time Timestamp indicating the time at which the intervention was initiated.
  intervention_end_time timestamp Timestamp indicating the time at which the intervention was completed.


Table intervention_type
IdxField NameData TypeDescription
* intervention_type_id integer Primary key of this table; implemented as an auto-incrementing integer.
  intervention_name text Name of intervention. E.g. prone ventilation, inhaled nitric oxide, tracheostomy, extracorporeal support.


Table lab_data

Contains data related to laboratory tests.

IdxField NameData TypeDescription
* patient_site_uid char(128) Identifier referencing a specific individual in the patient_data table.
* lab_data_id integer Primary key of this table; implemented as an auto-incrementing integer.
  lab_name text Name of laboratory test. Lower case letters, words separated by underscores.
  lab_loinc_code text LOINC code for the laboratory test.
  lab_cerner_code text Code for laboratory test.

Reference (for CERNER): https://bit.ly/2UGF5pp
  lab_units text Reporting units for the lab test.
  lab_sample_time timestamp Timestamp indicating the time at which the laboratory test was sampled.
  lab_sample_type text Type of specimen sample. Possible values: "venous_blood", "arterial_blood", "capillary_blood", "urine", "other", etc.
  lab_result_status text Current status of the culture. Possible values: "resulted", "cancelled", "pending".
  lab_result_time timestamp Timstamp indicating the time at which the laboratory test was resulted.
  lab_result_value float Value of the laboratory result, as a floating-point number. The lower or upper limit of the detectable value is used for extreme results (e.g. < 0.01 is encoded as 0.01).
  lab_result_value_string text Value of the laboratory result, as a string. Can include special characters, e.g. "< 0.06"


Table observation_data
IdxField NameData TypeDescription
* patient_site_uid char(128) Identifier referencing a specific individual in the patient_data table.
* observation_data_id integer Primary key of this table; implemented as an auto-incrementing integer.
* observation_type_id integer
  observation_device text Device that was used to perform the observation. E.g. "blood_pressure_cuff", "arterial_line".
  observation_source text Description of which source system the observation was drawn from (e.g. from lab data, Oacis, SIURGE, etc.)
  observation_start_time time Timestamp indicating the time at which the observation started.
  observation_end_time timestamp Timestamp indicating the time at which the observation ended. Empty if the observation is made at a single point in time.
  observation_value float Value of the observation, as a floating point number.
  observation_value_string text Observation value, as a string.


Table observation_type
IdxField NameData TypeDescription
* observation_type_id integer Primary key of this table; implemented as an auto-incrementing integer.
  observation_type_class smallint Values:
1 = Observation from clinical interaction only (e.g. capillary refill)
2 = Observation derived from a score or rule (e.g. AVPU scale)
3 = Observation from a measurement device (e.g. blood pressure)
4 = Observation derived from a setting on a device (e.g. PEEP)
* observation_type_name text Name of observation (e.g. temperature, heart rate).
* observation_units text Units for this type of observation.
  observation_regexp text Regular expression used to validate observations.


Table patient_data

Table for temporally invariant patient characteristics.

IdxField NameData TypeDescription
* patient_site_uid char(128) Per-site unique identifier, generated deterministically from unique local site ID via PBKDF2.

Procedure for generation: https://bit.ly/39ANAXa
* patient_global_uid char(128) Primary key of this table. Globally unique identifier for a patient with a given RAMQ number. Generated deterministically from RAMQ number via PBKDF2. Not traceable back to patient; follows NIST best practices for cryptographically secure storage of password keys.

Procedure for generation: https://bit.ly/39ANAXa
  patient_site_code text Standardized code for the site at which the data was acquired. Lowercase letters.

Reference codes: https://bit.ly/2Jyw7nN
  patient_was_transferred boolean True if the patient was transferred from another institution.
  patient_transfer_site_code text Site code of the transferring institution, if the patient has been transferred from elsewhere.
  patient_covid_status text COVID status of the patient. Possible values: "negative", "positive", "recovered", "unknown"
  patient_birth_date date Birth date of the patient. Should be replaced by patient_age, computed as per the most recent birth date, in de-identified data exports.
  patient_sex text Possible values: "male", "female", "other".
  patient_birth_country char(2) Country of origin, as 2-letter ISO 3166 code (e.g. CA).
  patient_ethnicity smallint Ethnicity of the patient, as defined by WHO CRF.
1 = Arab
2 = Black
3 = East Asian
4 = South Asian
5 = West Asian
6 = Latin American
7 = White
8 = Aboriginal / First Nations
9 = Other
10 = Unknown
  patient_pregnant boolean True if the patient was pregnant at the time of COVID testing.
  patient_postal_district char(3) First 3 letters of postal code of the patient (e.g. H3V).
  patient_assisted_living boolean True if the patient was living in an assisted living facility (semi-autonomous residence or long-term care facility) at the time of COVID testing.
  patient_code_status smallint Level of intervention, where:
1 = full code
2 = intubation, but no code
3 = medical therapy only
4 = comfort care only
  patient_vital_status text Vital status of the patient at the time of most recent follow-up. Possible values: "dead", "alive", "unknown"
  patient_last_fu_date date Date of last follow-up at which the mortality status of the patient was assessed.


Table pcr_data
IdxField NameData TypeDescription
* patient_site_uid char(128) Identifier referencing a specific individual in the patient_data table.
* pcr_data_id integer Primary key of this table; implemented as an auto-incrementing integer.
  pcr_name text Name of the PCR test being performed. Lowercase letters, words separated by underscores. E.g. "sars_cov2", "varicella_zoster_virus".
  pcr_loinc_code text LOINC code identifying the test kit used for PCR testing. If a non-commercial kit was used, the appropriate code is 94500-6.

Reference: https://bit.ly/2wQJfly
  pcr_sample_time timestamp Timestamp indicating the time at which the sample was drawn.
  pcr_sample_type text Type of sample collected. E.g. "nasopharyngeal_swab", "oropharyngeal_swab", "expectorated_sputum", "bronchial_secretions", "bronchoalveolar_lavage", "rectal_swab", "urine", "blood", "unknown".
  pcr_result_time timestamp Timestamp indicating the time at which the PCR test was resulted.
  pcr_result_status text Status of the PCR. Possible values: "resulted", "pending", "cancelled".
  pcr_result_value text Result of the PCR, if available. Possible values: "positive", "negative".
  pcr_result_transferred boolean True if the PCR was transferred from another site.


Table signal_data

Raw signal data (e.g. EKG, pulse oximeter, arterial line)

IdxField NameData TypeDescription
* patient_site_uid char(128) Identifier referencing a specific individual in the patient_data table.
* signal_data_id integer Primary key of this table; implemented as an auto-incrementing integer.
  signal_name text Type of signal being recorded. E.g. "arterial_blood_pressure", "pulse_oximetry", "electrocardiogram".
  signal_num_channels smallint The number of channels in the signal being recorded.
  signal_sampling_freq float Sampling frequency, in hertz.
  signal_data_uri text Unique resource identifier pointing to the file on disk where the signal is stored.
  signal_start_time timestamp Timestamp indicating when the signal recording started.
  signal_end_time text Timestamp indicating when the signal recording ended.


Table slice_data

Diagnostic imaging data in DICOM format (X-ray, CT, ultrasound).

IdxField NameData TypeDescription
* patient_site_uid char(128) Identifier referencing a specific individual in the patient_data table.
imaging_data_id integer Identifier that references the imaging study to which this slice belongs.
  imaging_accession_uid char(128) Hashed accession number of the imaging on the site's local PACS database.
* slice_data_id bigint Primary key of this table; implemented as an auto-incrementing integer.
  slice_series_instance_uid char(128) Hash of the series instance UID, as defined by the DICOM SeriesInstanceUID header (0020,000E).
  slice_study_instance_uid char(128) Hash of the study instance UID, as defined in DICOM headers.
  slice_data_uri text Unique resource identifier pointing to file containing the pixel data. The file on disk representing the pixel data is a matrix of 32-bit integers stored in HDF5 format (.H5).
  slice_view_position text As defined by the DICOM ViewPosition header (DICOM standard, C.8.1.1). Possible values: AP, PA, LL, RL, RLD, LLD, RLO, LLO.
  slice_patient_position text As defined by the DICOM PatientPosition header (DICOM standard C.7.3.1). Possible values: HFP, HFS, HFDR, HFDL, FFDR, FFDL, FFP, FFS, LFP, LFS, RFP, RFS, AFDR, AFDL, PFDR, PFDL.
  slice_image_orientation text Specifies the direction cosines of the first row and the first column with respect to the patient, as defined by the DICOM ImageOrientation header (DICOM standard C.7.6.2).

Should be: a string containing a comma-separated list of 6 floating point numbers.
  slice_image_position text Specifies the X, Y, and Z coordinates of the upper left hand corner of the image, as defined by the DICOM ImagePosition header (DICOM standard C.7.6.2)

Should be: a string containing a comma-separated list of 3 floating point numbers.
  slice_window_center float As defined by the DICOM WindowCenter header.
  slice_window_width float As defined by the DICOM WindowWidth header.
  slice_pixel_spacing text For CT scans only. As defined in the PixelSpacing DICOM header.
  slice_thickness float For CT scans only. As defined in the PixelSpacing DICOM header.
  slice_rows integer Number of rows in the slice image (height of the image), in pixels.
  slice_columns integer Number of columns in the slice image (width of the image), in pixels.
  slice_rescale_intercept float Rescale intercept, as defined by DICOM file.
  slice_rescale_slope float Rescale slope, as defined by DICOM file.


Table symptom_data

Data for symptoms experienced by the patient.

IdxField NameData TypeDescription
* patient_site_uid char(128) Identifier referencing a specific individual in the patient_data table.
* symptom_data_id integer Primary key of this table; implemented as an auto-incrementing integer.
  symptom_snomed_code text SNOMED CT code representing the symptom.
  symptom_name text Name of the symptom experienced.
  symptom_details text Free text containing any additional details about symptoms experienced.
  symptom_source text Data source system from which the symptom was recorded. For local institutional usage.
  symptom_start_time timestamp Timestamp indicating the time at which the symptoms started.
  symptom_end_time timestamp Timestamp indicating the time at which the symptoms ended.
